From: MIRA beta-readiness orchestrator (Lens A re-audit, 2026-06-08)
Subject: [PATCH] security(hub): rate-limit public /api/quickstart/ask LLM endpoint
SUPERSEDES: 2026-06-07-quickstart-rate-limit.patch (that file had malformed @@
            hunk counts and no longer `git apply`s — DO NOT use it; use this one).

WHY: /api/quickstart/ask is unauthenticated and fires a cascadeComplete (Groq->
Cerebras->Gemini, all shared free-tier) on every POST. No throttle => one script
drains the provider quota for the whole beta cohort (cost + denial-of-service).
Per-IP-hash in-memory limiter (20 req/IP/min), mirroring /api/public/report's
proven IP-hash approach. In-memory is per-instance; the hub runs as ONE container
today (root CLAUDE.md Container Map) so this is sufficient for the beta gate. Port
to a shared store/quickstart_rate table if the hub scales horizontally.

APPLY:
  cd <repo-root-MIRA>
  git checkout -b fix/quickstart-rate-limit
  git apply wiki/orchestrator/patches/2026-06-08-quickstart-rate-limit.patch

VERIFY:
  cd mira-hub && npx tsc --noEmit            # types clean (uses existing node_modules; do NOT install)
  # functional: 21st POST within 60s from one IP must return HTTP 429
  for i in $(seq 1 21); do curl -s -o /dev/null -w "%{http_code}\n" \
    -X POST localhost:3200/api/quickstart/ask \
    -H 'content-type: application/json' -d '{"question":"test"}'; done | tail -3

